    <td><font face="Times New Roman"><u><b></u></font><strong><font face="Arial" size="4">FACILITY
    SUMMARY REPORT</b></font></strong><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><i><p>What can
    this report do for you?</i></p>
    <div align="center"><center><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75%">
      <tr>
        <td width="5%" valign="top">1.</td>
        <td width="50%">Summarize the overall number of referrals for a specific hospital or
        region.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td width="5%" valign="top">2.</td>
        <td width="50%">Identify the number of patients meeting appropriate age and medical
        criteria for donation and the consent and recovery outcomes.</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    </center></div><p>The Facility Summary report is a summary of the referrals for specific
    referral facilities. The report will summarize the number of appropriate, approached,
    consented and recovered referrals. The report can be printed to reflect numbers or
    percentages (see examples).</p>
    <p>The column headings from left to right are Referral Facility, # of Total Referrals (the
    number of referral calls that Statline took), Appropriate (donation options that are
    appropriate according to the criteria received from the recovery agency), Approach
    (specific options that were approached for donation), Consent (specific options that the
    next of kin consented to for donation), and Recovery (specific options that were recovered
    for transplant or research). The Appropriate, Approach, Consent and Recovery categories
    are broken down into sub categories by specific types (O for organ, B for bone, ST for
    soft tissue, SK for skin, HV for heart valves and E for eyes). </p>
    <p>The total number of referrals by facility is listed on the left side of the report. To
    the right of each total referral number, the appropriate, approached, consented, and
    recovered referrals.</font></td>
  </tr>
</table>
